    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-04T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-04T20:00:00-05:00" n="144"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2733: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-04T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 4, 1933—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 4—8:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Department’s No. 3, January 4, 11 a.m.<note n="3a" xml:id="d144fn3a">See
                        footnote 2, above.</note> In two conversations with the Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs he has reiterated that he has <pb facs="0330" n="242" xml:id="pg_242"/>
                    reached no conclusion. Conversations with interested colleagues confirm this but
                    suggest that he is awaiting some indication from the Argentine. Have appointment
                    with him tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
